stylometry: Managers must figure out whether to have individual lines for each employee (and how many employees), or to have one large line that moves to the next available employee.  There is a waiting cost for customers, and it may be higher or lower when using a single line as apposed to multiple ones.  One cost would be how many employees are needed and how much they are paid.  An extensive cost would be is a customer decided not to purchase anything due to the length of the line.  The objective is to find a balance between waiting time and the number of employees used to maximize profits.
